# Selko HEP — Integration & Debug Log (handoff for Evan)

This covers everything done to take Evan's original HEP builder (standalone
app with placeholder Supabase config) and get it running live at
`hep.selko360.com` inside the shared Selko multi-tenant Supabase project.

## Repo state
- `metromobilehc-beep/selko-hep` on GitHub, deployed to Vercel, domain
  `hep.selko360.com` connected via CNAME in Namecheap.
- Files: `index.html`, `selko-hep-app.js`, `selko-hep-data.js`,
  `selko-hep-styles.css`, `images/` (28 exercise photos — originally
  uploaded nested inside `images_1/images` and `images_2/images` from two
  separate zips; flattened into one top-level `images/` folder since the
  code expects flat paths like `images/ex_0001_....png`).

## What changed from Evan's original code

### 1. Multi-tenancy (biggest structural change)
Original code had **no `company_id` anywhere** — every clinician who
logged in would've seen every program from every company. Selko's
existing modules (Cred, Comply, Billing) all isolate data by `company_id`
via a shared `profiles` table and a `get_my_company_id()` SQL helper.
HEP now follows the same pattern:

- New `loadCompanyContext()` function (runs right after login): looks up
  `company_id` from `profiles`, then checks `companies.has_hep`. If
  `has_hep` isn't `true` for that company, the user is logged back out
  with a message instead of silently seeing wrong/no data.
- `company_id` is now included on every `hep_programs` insert (required
  by the RLS `WITH CHECK` policy — inserts fail without it).

**DB migration run (in Supabase SQL editor, `selko-prod` project,**
**`zxserlkhwkfoqiepurdr.supabase.co`):**
```sql
CREATE TABLE hep_programs (
  id uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  company_id uuid NOT NULL REFERENCES companies(id),
  clinician_id uuid NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  name text NOT NULL,
  exercises jsonb NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]'::jsonb,
  code text NOT NULL,
  phone text NOT NULL,
  expiry timestamptz NOT NULL,
  compliance_days integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  created_at timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
);
-- RLS enabled, policies scope select/insert/update/delete to
-- company_id = get_my_company_id() for authenticated clinicians,
-- plus separate anon policies so patients (who only have a 4-digit
-- code, no login) can read/update their own program by code.
```
Metro's `company_id`: `b00ca9bc-d669-492d-8ad5-2d2783321ade`
`companies.has_hep` is now `true` for Metro.

Note: the original code's header comment mentioned `hep_exercises`,
`hep_patients`, `hep_shares` tables — those were never actually used
anywhere in the code (it only ever reads/writes `hep_programs`), so they
were dropped from the plan rather than built for nothing. If a real need
for separate patient records or a shares-mapping table comes up later,
that's a genuine schema addition, not something we're missing today.

### 2. Patient photo/video storage
Original code stored patient photos/videos as **base64 data URLs**
directly inside the `exercises` jsonb column. That bloats rows fast and
isn't how any other Selko module handles file uploads.

Replaced with a real Supabase Storage bucket: `hep-media` (public-read,
authenticated-write, folder-scoped by `company_id` so one company can't
write into another's folder). New `uploadPatientMedia()` function
uploads the file and stores just the public URL string in the jsonb
column instead of the raw base64.

Path convention: `hep-media/{company_id}/{clinician_id}/{exerciseId}_{photo|video}_{timestamp}.{ext}`

### 3. Login / session bugs found and fixed live
Several real bugs surfaced only once this was actually running against
real Supabase + real DNS + a real deploy — worth flagging clearly since
they're bugs in the original logic, not integration artifacts:

- **`onLoginSuccess()` wasn't awaited** on session restore (page
  refresh with an existing session) — fixed by awaiting it properly so
  `loadCompanyContext()` finishes before the app tries to render.
- **`showScreen()` never removed the baked-in `hidden` class.** Every
  authenticated screen (`screen-home`, `screen-programs`, etc.) starts
  with `class="screen app-screen hidden"` in the HTML, and the CSS
  defines `.hidden { display: none !important; }`. The old
  `showScreen()` only toggled the `active` class and set an inline
  `display` style — but `!important` always beats an inline style, so
  every authenticated screen stayed permanently invisible. This is why
  login "worked" (auth succeeded, no console errors) but the screen
  below the header was blank. Fixed by having `showScreen()` explicitly
  add/remove the `hidden` class on top of the `active` class.
- **Password recovery had no actual "set new password" step.**
  Supabase's `resetPasswordForEmail()` + clicking the emailed link logs
  the person into a temporary session automatically (normal Supabase
  behavior) — but the original `PASSWORD_RECOVERY` auth-state handler
  was empty (`// Handled by redirectTo in handleForgotPassword`, but
  nothing actually handled it). That meant anyone who clicked a reset
  link got dropped straight into the live app without ever being
  prompted to set a new password — a real access-control gap, not just
  a UX miss. Fixed by:
  - Adding a real `screen-new-password` screen (email/new
    password/confirm password fields)
  - Detecting the recovery redirect (`?reset=true` in the URL, or
    `type=recovery` in the hash) at page load and routing to that
    screen instead of falling through to the normal auto-login check
  - Wiring the `PASSWORD_RECOVERY` auth event to also show that screen
    (belt-and-suspenders in case the event fires before the URL check)
  - New `handleSetNewPassword()` calls `db.auth.updateUser({ password })`
    and only then logs the user into the app for real

### 4. Config
- `SUPABASE_URL` filled in with the real `selko-prod` project URL.
- `SUPABASE_ANON` — **still needs the real key pasted in from Supabase →
  Project Settings → API.** This has been the placeholder value more
  than once during this process (each time I regenerate the full file
  from my working copy, it resets to the placeholder — if you're
  re-pulling files from me, always re-check/re-paste this line before
  pushing).
- Required CDN scripts added to `index.html` (were missing entirely):
  Supabase JS v2 (`@supabase/supabase-js@2`) and SortableJS.
- The `selko-icon.png` logo file doesn't exist — rather than invent a
  logo, the broken `<img>` tags were just removed; the "selko" text
  wordmark next to each one still shows fine on its own. If you get a
  real icon file later, it can be dropped back in.

## Known gaps / not yet built
- **`send-sms` Supabase Edge Function doesn't exist.** The code calls it
  when a clinician sends a program to a patient, but there's no
  function deployed and no SMS provider (Twilio or similar) wired in
  yet. Programs save fine; the "text the patient" step will silently
  fail until this is built.
- **4-digit patient code is the only credential**, no rate limiting —
  fine for the UX (easy for patients to type on a phone) but worth
  knowing it's not a strong secret if this ever needs to be hardened.
- **Compliance streak tracking is `localStorage`-only** on the
  patient's device — works for same-device return visits, resets on a
  new device or cleared browser data. Fixing this properly means adding
  real patient identity, which is a bigger design conversation.
- **`hep_exercises` isn't a DB table** — the exercise library lives as a
  static `EXERCISE_LIBRARY` array in `selko-hep-data.js`, shared across
  all companies. Fine as-is unless there's a need for per-company custom
  exercises later.

## Reference — Selko multi-tenant pattern (for building anything else)
- Project: `selko-prod` — `https://zxserlkhwkfoqiepurdr.supabase.co`
- Every table: `company_id uuid NOT NULL REFERENCES companies(id)`, RLS
  enabled, policies scoped through `get_my_company_id()` (reads
  `company_id` off the `profiles` table for `auth.uid()`)
- `companies` table: one row per client, `has_[module]` feature flags
  gate access per module
- `profiles` table: `id` = `auth.uid()`, plus `company_id`, `role`,
  `email`, `full_name`, `is_super_admin`
- New users: created directly in Supabase Auth dashboard (Authentication
  → Users → Create new user, uncheck "send invite"), then a matching
  `profiles` row inserted manually or via each module's invite flow
